<bug_when>2017-03-01 09:32:39 -0500</bug_when>
<thetext>When a dnf update occurs (such as via a dnf-automatic timer), old (running) kernels are deliberately retained even if new kernels are also installed. This is great. What&apos;s not great is that kernel-related packages like kernel-devel may
get the upgrade (remove + install-new) treatment, even though -they- are needed too. Please consider protecting by default all kernel-* related packages for the running version, not just kernel[core].</thetext>
</long_desc>
